<subSubSection id="99A8657299162B24BF79FAC2FC25F9DD" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D10D36F999162B27BF79FAC2FB97F967" blockId="17.[826,1429,1340,1948]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">
Diagnosis — Female (Male unknown): Character states of family 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99162B27B846FAA1FBA4FAE8" authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1900" box="[1029,1133,1375,1399]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pionidae</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="B5234B0899162B27B8F7FAA1FAF1FAE8" author="Cook D. R." box="[1204,1336,1375,1399]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" pagination="1 - 860" refId="ref15906" refString="Cook D. R. 1974 - Water mite genera and subgenera - Mem. Amer. Ent. Inst., 21: 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">Cook 1974</bibRefCitation>
). Dorsum soft. All coxal setae slender, not spatulate; medial margin of Cx-III almost as long as medial margin of Cx-IV, posterior margin of Cx-IV concave, without angular projections. Genital bay very shallow, gonopore very long, genital plates broad and rounded, much smaller than gonopore, with 5 pairs of acetabula. P-3 with a very long lateral seta, P-4 with a peg-like mediodistal seta, ventral setae not associated with tubercles (
<figureCitation id="49892A7C99162B27B83BF965FB3BF92C" box="[1144,1266,1691,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="19.[159,171,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[252,1338,451,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-6@19.[242,1346,451,1711]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11: Schwoerbelia pioniformis n. gen., n. sp., female, Bach MAE National Park, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – gnathosoma; E – I-L-5 and -6; F – IV-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396012/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Figures 11</figureCitation>
B-C); gnathosoma with posterior anchoral process. Legs slender, swimming setae present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999162B27BF23F8EEFAB8F8B7" blockId="17.[826,1429,1340,1948]" box="[864,1393,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">
<typeStatus id="0E09885B99162B27BF23F8EEFC50F8B7" box="[864,921,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Type</typeStatus>
species — 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99162B27B858F8EEFAE1F8B7" authority="Pešic &amp; Smit, 2016" authorityName="Pešic &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2016" box="[1051,1320,1808,1832]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Schwoerbelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pioniformis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99162B27B858F8EEFAE1F8B7" box="[1051,1320,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Schwoerbelia pioniformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99162B27B96CF8EEFAB8F8B7" bold="true" box="[1327,1393,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F8F5579099162B27B96CF8EEFAB8F8B7" box="[1327,1393,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999162B27BF23F8C0FA5DF803" blockId="17.[826,1429,1340,1948]" pageId="17" pageNumber="409">Etymology — The genus name is in honour of Jürgen Schwoerbel (1930-2002), who described one of the pionid subfamilies. Moreover, he was one of</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999152B24BCDCFF04FE95FE92" blockId="18.[159,348,250,269]" box="[159,348,250,269]" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Peši´c V. and Smit H.</paragraph>
<caption id="85CD667199152B24BCDCFB81FE53FB32" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396008" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5396008" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396008/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" startId="18.[159,171,1151,1170]" targetBox="[242,1346,302,1118]" targetPageId="18">
<paragraph id="D10D36F999152B24BCDCFB81FE53FB32" blockId="18.[159,1429,1150,1197]" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">
FIGURE 10: 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24BD52FB80FDCAFB0E" authority="" authorityName="Vidrine" authorityYear="1993" box="[273,515,1150,1169]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Majumderatax">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24BD52FB80FEB9FB0E" box="[273,368,1150,1169]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Unionicola</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24BD3EFB80FDCAFB0E" box="[381,515,1150,1169]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Majumderatax)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., deutonymph, Mekong River, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars – 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999152B24BCDCFB10FE0FFAD3" blockId="18.[159,762,1262,1356]" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">the editors of a new standard work on European water mites, published in the series &quot;Süsswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa&quot;.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999152B24BC86FA88FC25F9DD" blockId="18.[159,762,1398,1949]" lastBlockId="18.[826,1429,1262,1602]" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">
Remarks — Due to the following characters: medial margin of posterior coxal plates formed jointly by Cx-III and Cx-IV, all setae on Cx-II and -III fine, not thickened, gnathosoma ventral margin posteriorly projecting in an anchoral process (in ventral view bifurcate as in 
<figureCitation id="49892A7C99152B24BDCBF9D8FDC5F9A1" box="[392,524,1574,1598]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="19.[159,171,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[252,1338,451,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-6@19.[242,1346,451,1711]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11: Schwoerbelia pioniformis n. gen., n. sp., female, Bach MAE National Park, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – gnathosoma; E – I-L-5 and -6; F – IV-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396012/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Figure 11D</figureCitation>
), and P-4 with a distoventral peg-like seta, the female of new species resembles to those of genus 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24BD9AF993FDDEF91B" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[473,535,1645,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Piona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24BD9AF993FDDEF91B" box="[473,535,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Piona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However the single female from a stream in 
<collectingCountry id="A9A5766999152B24BDA5F971FD80F938" box="[486,585,1679,1703]" name="Vietnam" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
is unique in P- 3 with a very long lateral seta, exceeding the tip of P-5. In all known members of subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24BED0F92BFF11F88F" authority="Thor" authorityName="Thor" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pioninae">Pioninae Thor</taxonomicName>
lateral setae on P-3 are short. The new genus resembles 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24BD5FF8E5FE0BF8AC" box="[284,450,1819,1843]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Huitfeldtiinae">Huitfeldtiinae</taxonomicName>
(P-3 with a very long lateral seta) which in addition to 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24BE47F8C0FD30F8C9" authority="Thor, 1900" authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1900" box="[516,761,1854,1878]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Huitfeldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24BE47F8C0FDB3F8C9" box="[516,634,1854,1878]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Huitfeldtia</emphasis>
Thor, 1900
</taxonomicName>
(Holarctic), includes 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24BDDBF89CFDBBF8E6" authority="Harvey, 1996" authorityName="Harvey" authorityYear="1996" box="[408,626,1889,1914]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Larri" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24BDDBF89CFE06F8E6" box="[408,463,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Larri</emphasis>
Harvey, 1996
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="A9A5766999152B24BEC0F89FFD3BF8E6" box="[643,754,1889,1913]" name="Australia" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Australia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24BC94F87AFDF1F802" authority="Smith &amp; Cook, 2009" authorityName="Smith &amp; Cook" authorityYear="2009" box="[215,568,1924,1949]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Gereckea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24BC94F87AFEFCF803" box="[215,309,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Gereckea</emphasis>
Smith &amp; Cook, 2009
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="A9A5766999152B24BE0FF87AFD62F803" box="[588,683,1924,1948]" name="Canada" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Canada</collectingCountry>
). The new genus differs in slender, not spatulate coxal setae (present in 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99152B24B847FAEFFBB3FAB6" authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1900" box="[1028,1146,1297,1321]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Huitfeldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24B847FAEFFBB3FAB6" box="[1028,1146,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Huitfeldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), posterior margin concave, without acute-angled apodemes, and a small peg, not a prominent spine-like mediodistal seta on P-4 (see 
<bibRefCitation id="B5234B0899152B24BF90FA85FB7CFA0D" author="Smith I. M. &amp; Cook D. R. &amp; Gerecke R." box="[979,1205,1402,1427]" pageId="18" pageNumber="410" pagination="111 - 156" refId="ref16552" refString="Smith I. M., Cook D. R., Gerecke R. 2015 - Revision of the status of some genus-level water mite taxa in the families Pionidae Thor, 1900, Aturidae Thor, 1900, and Nudomideopsidae Smith, 1990 (Acari: Hydrachnidiae) - Zootaxa, 3919: 111 - 156" type="journal article" year="2015">
Smith 
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99152B24B866FA85FBA9FA0C" box="[1061,1120,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). In most pionid groups, characters (sexual dimorphism on leg segments) important for classification are restricted to males. However the unique features of female from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A5766999152B24BF79F9F9FC54F980" box="[826,925,1543,1567]" name="Vietnam" pageId="18" pageNumber="410">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
are large enough to warrant the erection of the new genus.
</paragraph>
